			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">An enchanter should be able to reliably and regularly crowd control 2 mobs in a zone where an equivilently geared tank can tank a single slowed mob with a cleric chain-chealing him or the tank being blast-healed with an unslowed mob.
<br />

<br />
Alternatively, an equivilently geared enchanter and bard should be equally good options for crowd control.  This includes the bard's out-of-camp crowd control (pulling singles), which a bard currently is the master of.  (the enchanter need not crowd control <span style="font-weight: bold">the same</span> as a bard -- but, the bard's (out-of-camp plus in-camp) CC abilities should be no better than the enchanters (out-of-camp plus in-camp) CC abilities.
<br />

<br />
Do these standards make sense?  Is requesting these standards unreasonable?
<br />

<br />
I do no believe enchanters pass the above standards.  Without passing the above standards, I believe that enchanter crowd control is nothing more than a toy.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
