			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Take it down to nuts and bolts:
<br />

<br />
A single creature should not be able to dps to death a prepared, level-appropriate geared enchanter in the time it takes to target and cast two (possibly three) casts of the level appropriate CC spell.
<br />

<br />
Similarly, two (possibly three) l.a. creatures should not be able to kill him in 1 cast of it.
<br />

<br />
Full Preparation should take no more time than average pulls--say 90 seconds, or two minutes maximum.
<br />

<br />
It's that simple, really.  The way our current mitigation works is binary.  Either you can live long enough to cast twice, or you die.  The -only- way you can currently live long enough is to raid content past where you are effective.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
