				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just occured to me a couple of ways to possibly add a little extra functionality to mezzes.  Remove the LOS requirement and increase the range.  I don't see why mezzing a mob from far away and around a corner would be game-breaking, it's not like anyone can kill it.   It allows us some room to try again on resist, and it allows us to mezz mobs based off of a puller's target.  I won't need to wait to see my targets when the paladin puller says 'inc 3', especially if there is not much visible room and he is coming around a corner or down some stairs.    It also remedies the situation where a mob paths around a small object like an urn and we end up with that 'Target cannot be seen'.
<br />

<br />
