				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In regards to Yakk's post, I'm thinking he is referring to mostly single group situations. If that is true, I like to think a chanter can pull as well as or quite often outpull bards so I am not sure the standard applies. I won't claim to be able to pull a mob past other mobs like a good bard can, though. But if all you're doing is getting mob after mob after mob for an experience camp or clearing your way to a certain place, I'll go against a bard any day. I had a rogue joke last night in a Hive instance that he almost had time for a nap when I was 10 seconds late to the group with the next mob. It was the only time they killed one and did not have a debuffed one standing next to them waiting to die in an entire hour of non-stop killing. Exceptions, rare ones, are probably out there, and I bet Yakk can reply with a reference to a zone or spot in a zone where the bard would be preferred.
<br />

<br />
The offtanking adds on raids issue is a sad one. I deal with it regularly, too. The thing I say to convince raid leadership to allow more reliance on mezzing is that we can accomplish certain raids with fewer folks than would be needed if you wanted to offtank. If I'm holding 1, 2, 3, or 4 mobs mezzed allowing everyone else to focus DPS on the main target, it means we don't need all those other tanks and healers so we still get to do things on nights when not a lot of folks are on. The MPG trial that spits adds out, half or so are mezzable, while all you have to do is outlast the main mob comes to mind, Endurance I think. I recently held 6 mobs almost the entire fight. Why offtank all 4 ukuns during the first big fight in Tacvi when you can mez the manasipper and root 2 of the others in a corner? Offtanking just one of those bad boys is WAY more doable than offtanking 4.
<br />

<br />
Same reasoning on charm in a few cases.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
