			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">few ideas:
<br />
1. allow spell casting deftness to work on detrimental spells.
<br />
2. allow spells with a 2.5 sec cast time to be spellhasted, or give us 3.0 second casting mez spells. (would cast faster than our current ones do, with spell haste)
<br />
3. give us an innate dispel, insta click aa skill.
<br />
4. give us an innate tashan, insta click aa skill.
<br />

<br />
Then, we could cast a mez.  if it fails, we could strip the mob of buffs, and tash it, in the time it takes our mez spell to refresh.  If spellhastable, that would put us at just over 4 seconds to mez twice, tash, and strip buffs.  I think thats about the amount of time that a non-raid enchanter has vs. current content.
<br />

<br />
This is taking into account several assumptions.  one of which is, that SoE wont give enchanters (or mages/shaman) bigger debuffs, because then mobs would need more resistance to be competative.  Thats fine.  I don't want an innate tashan to reduce more than our current spell line, I just want get rid of the 3.25 seconds that it adds to our tanking time.
<br />

<br />
We also should get innate invis (like rangers and druids... we got invis before either of them did).   We should get innate dispel (how rangers got innate specialized dispel is lost on me).  We should get either an innate tashan, or an innate slow.  As the tashan debuff spells are not really scalable, thats the more "balanced" option, game-wise.
<br />

<br />
--
<br />
However, if we simply ask for those from sony, they'll of course water it down to nothing.  So, we hafta ask for more, and then "compromise" down to what we need.   So, the other things we should ask for include:
<br />
innate memory blur.  let it cost 400 mana, insta click and reusable instantly and... call it Fading Memory.  :P
<br />

<br />
An illusion: corpse spell.  We've all spent enough time in the fetal position to know darn well what it looks like.  Shouldn't be *that* hard to fake.
<br />

<br />
An aa skill for advanced channeling to cast on the run, equal to that of a level 1 bard.
<br />

<br />
An illusion: GM spell, so we can trick other players into sharing their camps with us.
<br />

<br />
Give us the ability to share our agro with someone.  You know, either that tank you love, or that healer you don't...  heh
<br />

<br />
That should just about do it.  :)<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tashim</a>
<br />
