<br />

<br />
Enchanters are highly dependant of the environment, where OoW was absolutely horrid in this regards with easy single pulls and where you need mez the mobs often resist and resist=dead ench.
<br />
This have changed drastically in DoDh, where CC is far more needed and resists are not nearly as bad, I know I enjoy playing my enchanter far more now than I did before DoDh because of this.
<br />

<br />
The same goes for raids where everything past GoD up until Vish requires no CC besides OTing, with a few exceptions like Zun in RCoD and OMM cause of charm.
<br />
In DP and Sendaii we use enchanters a lot, but I honestly dont think our enchanter team find some of the encounters all that thrilling since they reminds them of Rathe council just with a shorter duration, but they have really had to find that mez spell again.
<br />

<br />
The same can be said about charm, where the "old" charm became overpowered back before the xp nerf in PoP and the next step was the insane dps from charmed pets in tipt/vxed. It is indeed disapointing that no sollutions have been found, but I honestly think its partially the Ench comunity's fault in the sense that you seem to be fixed on an either full package or nothing. At least I read a post from a Dev on eqlive a while ago where he asked about how you would like it and one of the things he said was that he might remove the xp penalty. I cant offer a solution, but since nothing have happened in ages ( I might have missed it if you have change stance on it tho ) it might be time for you to try and see if you can get that discusion back on track and that might mean you have to change your wiev on what is acceptable.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
